## 10. Performance Optimization

### Vectorized Operations
```python
# Use pandas vectorized operations instead of loops
# GOOD
df['returns'] = df['close'].pct_change()
df['sma'] = df['close'].rolling(20).mean()

# AVOID
returns = []
for i in range(1, len(df)):
    returns.append((df.iloc[i]['close'] - df.iloc[i-1]['close']) / df.iloc[i-1]['close'])
```

### Efficient Data Handling
```python
# Use appropriate data types
df['volume'] = df['volume'].astype('int32')  # Instead of int64
df['price'] = df['price'].astype('float32')  # Instead of float64

# Use categorical for repeated strings
df['symbol'] = df['symbol'].astype('category')
```

